     "character": "Jane",
     "dialogue": "Hello everyone, today we're diving into the fascinating world of black holes. Our guest is Dr. Ada, an expert in astrophysics. Welcome, Dr. Ada!"
   },
   {
     "character": "Dr. Ada",
     "dialogue": "Thanks for having me, Jane."
   },
   {
     "character": "Jane",
     "dialogue": "So, let's start with the basics. What exactly is a black hole?"
   },
   {
     "character": "Dr. Ada",
     "dialogue": "Imagine a star so massive that even its own gravity can't keep it from collapsing in on itself."
   },
   {
     "character": "Jane",
     "dialogue": "Wow, that sounds terrifying! And we can't see them because of their gravity?"
   },
   {
     "character": "Dr. Ada",
     "dialogue": "Exactly. But they're not completely invisible. We can detect them by how they affect nearby matter."
   },
   {
     "character": "Jane",
     "dialogue": "Speaking of matter, what happens when something falls into a black hole?"
   },
   {
     "character": "Dr. Ada",
     "dialogue": "It gets stretched out and heated up so much that it evaporates due to Hawking radiation."
   },
   {
     "character": "Jane",
     "dialogue": "Evaporates? So they're not really black forever?"
   },
   {
     "character": "Dr. Ada",
     "dialogue": "Well, theoretically, no. But these evaporation times are incredibly long - far longer than the current age of the universe."
   },
   {
     "character": "Jane",
     "dialogue": "Let's wrap up with a mind-boggling fact about black holes. Dr. Ada?"
   },
   {
     "character": "Dr. Ada",
     "dialogue": "Black holes might be connected through wormholes, allowing them to merge across the universe."
   },
   {
     "character": "Jane",
     "dialogue": "That's incredible! Thanks for joining us today, Dr. Ada. And listeners, stay curious!"
   }
 ]
